    dc:title "The Luciolinae of S. E. Asia and the Australopacific region: a revisionary checklist (Coleoptera: Lampyridae) including description of three new genera and 13 new species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508102>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508104>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508196>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508106>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508108>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508112>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508115>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508119>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508121>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508123>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508127>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508131>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508135>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508137> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508102>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1−8. Key to genera characters 1. 1, 2 Australoluciola anthracina type male (MNHN); 3, 4 Aus. japenensis paratype male; 5, 6 Atyphella scabra male; 7, 8 Aty. leucura type male (MNHN). 1, 2, 5, 6 aedeagus ventral (1, 5), and dorsal (2, 6) (lateral lobes are arrowed). 3, 4, 7, 8 aedeagal sheath dorsal (3, 7), and ventral (4, 8). Oblique arrows in anterior section indicate point where tergite arms join the lateral margins of the sheath sternite; vertical arrow pointing to foot of page in 3 indicates anterior margin of sheath tergite; vertical and horizontal lines in 4 indicate length (vertical) and width (horizontal) of sheath sternite; lower paired arrows in 8 indicate emarginated margin of sheath sternite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508102/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508104>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9−16. Key to genera characters 2. 9. Missimia flavida type male; 10 Luciola brahmina type male (MNHN); 11, 12 Luciola seriata type male (CMG); 13 Asymmetricata circumdata male; 14, 15 Kuantana menayah gen. et sp. nov.; 16 Curtos costipenis male. 9 anterior head (arrow indicates clypeus); 10, 11, 16 dorsal (arrows in 16 indicate humeral carina); 12 lateral tergite 8 aedeagal sheath and sclerites); 13 dorsal tergites 7 and 8; 14, 15, dorsal (14) and ventral tergite 8. Figure legends: AS aedeagal sheath; T7, 8 tergites 7, 8." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508104/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508196>
    dc:description "FIGURES 230−237. Kuantana menayah gen. et sp. nov. type male. 230, 232 habitus dorsal (232 slightly to side with right elytron pulled to side); 233−237 abdomen: 233 ventral. 234 dorsal, 235 right lateral; 236, 237 terminal abdomen tergites 7 8: 237 from beneath with aedeagus and sheath removed; 238 from above (left side of tergite 7 damaged in extraction). Scale lines are 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508196/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508106>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17−21. Key to genera characters 3. 17, 18 Triangulara frontoflava; 19 Pygatyphella obsoleta; 20, 21 Pygat. huonensis. 17 ventral whole body; 18, 19, 21 ventral terminal abdomen; 20 right lateral terminal abdomen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508106/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508108>
    dc:description "FIGURES 22−29. Key to genera characters 4. 22, 23, 26−28 Pacifica salomonis male; 24, 29 Pac. limbatipennis (Guadalcanal BPBM); 25 Pac. limbatifusca paratype male. 22, 24, 25 dorsal; 23 ventral; 26 aedeagus ventral; 27, 28 tergite 8 ventral and from right side showing ventral surface; upper arrows in 27, 28 indicate projections from anterior tergal arms; lower arrow in 27 indicates oblique ridge on ventral surface; 29 aedeagal sheath ventral (upper arrow indicates beginning of emargination, lower arrow indicates emargination." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508108/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508112>
    dc:description "FIGURES 30−37. Key to genera characters 5. 30, 34, 35 Pygatypella undulata; 31 Pygat. wisselmerenia; 32, 36 Pygat. obsoleta; 33 Pygat. peculiaris; 37 Pygat. kiunga paratype male. 30−34, 37 dorsal (34 diagrammatic representation of colour pattern); 35 aedeagal sheath, ventral; 36 aedeagus ventral, line outline." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508112/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508115>
    dc:description "FIGURES 38−43. Key to genera characters 6. 38, 43 Pygoluciola qingyu; 39, 40 Abscondita pallescens comb. nov.; 41, 42 Pygoluciola hamulata type male. 38−40 aedeagal sheath ventral (38, 39) and slightly right lateral (40) (arrows indicate position where lateral tergal arms join the median sternite); 41, 43 terminal abdomen ventral; 42 termnal abdomen left lateral. Figure legends: V7 ventrite 7; T8 tergite 8." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508115/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508119>
    dc:description "FIGURES 44–49. Key to genera characters 7. Luciola cerata lectotype aedeagus. 44, 47 dorsal; 45, 48 ventral (lobes arrowed); 46, 49 left lateral. Figs 47–49 outline diagrams of photos immediately above. Figure legend: ML median lobe; BP basal piece." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508119/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508121>
    dc:description "FIGURES 50–56. Key to genera characters 8. 50, 51 Pygoluciola satoi; 52, 53 Emeia pseudosauteri; 54, 55, 56 Aquatica ficta. 50, 51 aedeagus dorsal (50: arrow indicates separation in basal area of lateral lobes), and ventral; 52, 56 dorsal habitus; 53, 55 ventral habitus;; 54 aedeagal sheath ventral semidiagrammatic (arrows indicate pointed projections along sides of sheath sternite)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508121/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508123>
    dc:description "FIGURES 57–63. Key to genera characters 9. 57, 58 Atyphella aphrogeneia; 59 Lloydiella majuscula; 60, 61 Ll. japenensis; 62, 63 Convexa wolfi. 57, 58 aedeagal sheath dorsal (57) and ventral (arrows indicates emargination of right side of sheath sternite); 59 dorsal and ventral, and 63 dorsal habitus; 60–62 aedeagus, 60 slightly right lateral; 61, 62 ventral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508123/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508127>
    dc:description "FIGURES 64–69. Key to genera characters 10. 64 Aquilonia costata; 65, 66 Aq. similismessoria comb. nov.; 67 Magnalata limbata; 68 Atyphella flammans; 69 Aty. aphrogeneia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508127/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508131>
    dc:description "FIGURES 70–77. Key to genera characters 11. 70–72 Serratia sibuyania gen. et sp. nov.; 73–75 Emarginata trilucida gen. nov. et comb. nov.; 76, 77 Colophotia praeusta. 70, 72, 73 dorsal habitus (70 anterior body only); 74 ventral habitus; 71 dissected terminal abdomen ventral; 75 ventrite 7 and elytral apices from below; 76, 77 ventrites 6, 7 from left (76) and below (77). Figure legends: MC median carina; MPP median posterior projection; PLP posterolateral projections." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508131/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508135>
    dc:description "FIGURES 78–86. Key to genera characters 12. 78–80, 83 Inflata indica; 81 Medeopteryx cribellata; 82 Pyrophanes appendiculata; 84 Australoluciola flavicollis; 85 Aus. nigra; 86 Aus. anthracina. Figure legends: LL1 basal expanded portion of lateral lobes; LL2 apical narrowed portion of lateral lobes; ML median lobe." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508135/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508137>
    dc:description "FIGURES 87–95. Key to genera characters 13. 87–91 Pteroptyx macdermotti; 92, 93 Medeopteryx sp.; 94 Pteroptyx testacea; 95 Trisinuata caudabifurca. 87 left hind leg (without coxa) 88 right hind leg detail femur and tibia; 89–93 aedeagal sheath ventral (89, 91, 92), left lateral (90, 93) (paraprocts arrowed in 89–91); 94, 95 ventrites 6, 7 from beneath (incurving lobes arrowed in 95). Figure legend: LO light organs." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3508137/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

